			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I'm wondering if anyone else here has tried this, I read it somewhere but can't remember if it was on eqdiva or not. 
<br />

<br />
Basically, fighting Trak without a mage...everyone gathers in the banish room, bard runs up to the liar, fades to get rid of aggro, then aggros Trak and takes a beating until getting banished back down to the banish room where the rest of the raid is waiting. Trak slowly makes his way down to the banish room chasing after the bard, when he gets there raid tags him and bard fades to clear any additional aggro that Trak may of picked up on his way down.
<br />

<br />
So, that was my plan anyways. Well, first time we tried it we had a monk with us so I explained it to him and he did it flawlessly...banish, Trak came down, he fd, we killed Trak with a couple of adds that the chanter held down fine.
<br />

<br />
Now fast forward 3 days, we had monk again, he tried twice and Trak wouldn't come. Then one 3rd try he came, but we lost the battle. After regrouping and getting back down to banish room monk went again, but two more times couldn't get Trak to come and then had to camp for the night. I (bard) ran up to lair, took a beating, got banished...but Trak wouldn't come after me, does anyone know why? I didn't fade when I got back down, I just sat there waiting. I tried this 3 times, getting banished each time, and no Trak. The 4th time I tried he killed me before he banished me so that was it for the night.
<br />

<br />
Is there a secret to getting him to follow? I don't understand why sometimes he does and sometimes he doesn't. If anyone has tried this pulling method I'd love some ideas/advice.
<br />

<br />
Thanks!
<br />
Lydie
<br />
65 Bard of Eci</span></td>
