				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Trakanon<a name="65730"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 5 04 6:58 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">It will take you longer to set up, explain, and impliment your &quot;fancy pull&quot; to the banish point than it will to just kill Trak a his spawn point.</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
No, it doesn't. It is so much simpler and you don't need to clear the area around him. There is also much less of a chance of something going wrong. Unless you have massive overkill and can take him with all his friends at once, there's no point in taking chances. Nobody gets bansihed this way. Nothing unexpected.
<br />

<br />
Just clear to the bridge. Move your raid party to the banish spot. Aggro anything, Trak will come. Fade when he's on the bridge. Wait 30 secs or so for the rest to path back. Bellow him and lead him back, make sure he keeps up with you. If you pick up an add just fade it off. Trak tends to stay put, while everything else turns around and goes back to spawn fairly quickly. This is a simple pull, nothing tricky about it.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
